          SELECT "b"."BookId", "b"."DateWritten", "b"."IsAvailable", "b"."LanguageId", "b"."Price", "b0"."Id", "b0"."AuthorId", "b0"."GenreId", "b0"."Title"
          FROM "BookInfos" AS "b"
          INNER JOIN "Books" AS "b0" ON "b"."BookId" = "b0"."Id"

              SELECT l.Id, l.Name, t.BookId, t.DateWritten, t.IsAvailable, t.LanguageId, t.Price, t.Id, t.AuthorId, t.GenreId, t.Title
              FROM Languages AS l
              LEFT JOIN 
              (
                  SELECT b.BookId, b.DateWritten, b.IsAvailable, b.LanguageId, b.Price, b0.Id, b0.AuthorId, b0.GenreId, b0.Title
                  FROM BookInfos AS b
                  INNER JOIN Books AS b0 ON b.BookId == b0.Id
              ) AS t ON l.Id == t.LanguageId
              ORDER BY l.Name ASC, l.Id ASC, t.BookId ASC), 
          null, 
          Func<QueryContext, DbDataReader, ResultContext, SingleQueryResultCoordinator, Language>, 
          Bookstore.DAL.DatabaseApplicationContext, 
          False, 
          False, 
          True
      )'
